							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/channlertwyman/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/website-pic-2-scaled-e1701378158447-100x100.jpeg" width="100" height="100" alt="Channler Twyman" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/channlertwyman/">Channler Twyman</a></h6>
										Channler Twyman is a writer, scholar, and proud Georgia native. His works have appeared both in print and online on various websites and publishers. He has received support for his upcoming works through Tin House as a YA Scholar in 2021 and most recently as a Kimbilio Fellow. He's currently studying Fiction writing as an MFA student at Virginia Commonwealth University. You can follow him @/channwrites on all socials, or hit him up on his website, channwriteshere.com																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
							</div>
							<br class="clear"/>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div>
